ight: 16.7969px; text-align: center;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px; text-align: center;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Spellcasting Ability</h2>\n<p>Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your herald spells, since their power is derived from your dedication to your oath. You use your Charisma whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Charisma modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a herald spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier</p>\n<p><strong>Spell attack modifier</strong> = your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier</p>\n<h2>Spellcasting Focus</h2>\n<p>You can use a holy symbol as a spellcasting focus for your Herald spells.</p>",
